 considering whether I should delete an ineffective test because it only focuses on the active class, leaving other attempts uncovered. I know I should keep tests covering each dynamic-access class in dedicated Java test files, but this one doesn't reach the active class. I'm wondering if it's better to remove the file to avoid unrelated coverage. But then, the user wants to complete a task. There might be a workaround using the public API and Mockito extension, but I'll need to investigate more about how the active class behaves at runtime.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Analyzing testing options**\\n\\nI’m considering creating a test that uses the public API if I can catch errors for unsupported active behavior. But, wait, dynamic class loading isn't unsupported here. I wonder if running Java 8 could help, but it won't. I could try using the Mockito plugin system to load a custom class that shadows java.lang.Module, but that’s blocked due to the prohibited package. In native-image, there might be no java.lang.Module. Using system properties isn’t feasible either. I could compile a public top-level interface, but I'm not sure it’ll actually improve the active class's performance.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "I did not add another test for `MethodHandleProxy$LegacyVersion` because the remaining call sites are not reachable through Mockito’s supported public API on the current JDK/GraalVM runtime.\n\nRelevant Mockito 5.0.0 source path:\n\n- `ProxyRealMethod.make()` first selects `InvokeDefaultProxy` on Java 16+ because `InvocationHandler.invokeDefault(...)` exists.\n- `MethodHandleProxy.LegacyVersion` is only attempted after that fails.\n- Its constructor then explicitly rejects module-capable runtimes:\n\n```java\nClass.forName(\"java.lang.Module\");\nthrow new RuntimeException(\"Must not be used when modules are available\");\n```\n\nTherefore these two call sites remain Java-8-only fallback behavior:\n\n- `Constructor#newInstance(...)` at `MethodHandleProxy.java:63`\n- `Lookup#unreflectSpecial(...)` at `MethodHandleProxy.java:65`\n\nReaching them on this runtime would require forcing internal Mockito implementation selection or reflectively constructing `LegacyVersion`, which would violate the task rules requiring public API coverage and no direct test reflection.\n\nThe existing dedicated test file remains:\n\n- `tests/src/org.mockito/mockito-core/5.0.0/src/test/java/org_mockito/mockito_core/MethodHandleProxyInnerLegacyVersionTest.java`\n\nIt exercises the supported public default-interface-method proxy path, but it cannot make Mockito select the legacy Java 8 implementation on a module-capable JDK.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_01fc555f53abbb6f016a21d5db5354819692287363067e51ec\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 4719, "output": 1331, "cacheRead": 23040, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 29090, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1780602301211, "responseId": "resp_01fc555f53abbb6f016a21d5bec03481968b2fc2fc3a2951ae"}}
